course_name: Complete Python With DSA Bootcamp + LEETCODE Exercises
content:
Undoubtedly one of the best DSA courses out there.

Mayank and Krish have done an outstanding job. What truly sets this course apart is the tutor‚Äôs deep commitment to clarity ‚Äî he doesn‚Äôt just write code, he explains it again and again, even covering the tiniest details that most others assume you already know. That kind of patience and empathy for beginners is rare and absolutely commendable.

However, I‚Äôd like to humbly request the instructors to expand the course by adding a few core DSA topics that are currently missing. These are essential for interviews and problem-solving, and their inclusion would truly make this course a one-stop destination:

üîπ 1. Arrays
Sorting: QuickSort, MergeSort

Searching: Binary Search

Two Pointers: e.g., remove duplicates, partitioning- not covered 

Sliding Window: subarray sums, min/max in windows -not covered

üîπ 2. Linked Lists
Traversal

Insertion/Deletion at head, tail, position

Reversal (iterative + recursive)

Cycle Detection (Floyd‚Äôs Algorithm) -not covered we had just given a question to solve but havent practiced doubly linked list enough, can be improved

üîπ 3. Hash Tables (Maps & Sets)
Concept of hashing

Lookup/Insert/Delete

Collision handling

üîπ 4. Trees (BT & BST)
Inorder, Preorder, Postorder traversal

Recursive + Iterative approaches

BST Search, Insert -bfs and this not explained 

üîπ 5. Stacks & Queues
Operations: Push/Pop/Peek, Enqueue/Dequeue

Applications in expressions, BFS, etc.

üîπ 6. Heaps
Min/Max heap basics

Heapify & heap-building

Top-K problems using heaps

üîπ 7. Graphs
BFS & DFS (both iterative and recursive)

Dijkstra‚Äôs Algorithm

Cycle detection (DFS)

üîπ 8. Tries
Implement from scratch

Insert/Search/Prefix Matching

Autocomplete logic

üîπ 9. Union-Find
Disjoint Set operations

Path compression, Union by rank

Graph cycle detection

üîπ 10. Core Algorithm Techniques
Recursion: Base/recursive case, tree problems

Dynamic Programming: Memoization, Tabulation

Greedy Algorithms: Activity selection, coin problems

Backtracking: N-Queens, permutations, Sudoku  -not explained at all


DSA is about patterns recognising, this would be the best course ever if you guys may add the missing things. I have found many courses on dsa python on this platform all useless and explained by people who aren't even in the industry. but this course is so good, just wondering if i can buy some other course or you guys can please add it??
